# learning-project (monorepo)

Canonical human overview: [README.md](../../README.md). Agent entry doc: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md).

## Packages and stacks

- **`frontend/`** — CodeStep app: **Vite, React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind v4**. Course domains and walkthrough logic live under `frontend/src/domains/` (each subdomain may have a short `README.md`). Prefer matching existing patterns there for learner-facing UI and examples.
- **`beginner-js/`** — Topic folders with `tasks.js` / `tasks.test.js`. Root **`Makefile`** wraps **`bun test`** for topics and single-task targets (see Makefile comments).
- **`docs/codestep/`** — Product overview and phased specs (`overview.md`, `01.md`–`04.md`); use when changing CodeStep behavior or roadmap-shaped work.
- **`system-design/`** — Standalone static HTML/CSS/JS viewer; not part of the Vite app. Treat as a separate mini-site unless the task is explicitly there.
- **`data-structures/`** — Standalone static HTML/CSS/JS data structures roadmap (`css/`, `js/data/`, `js/demos/`); same mini-site pattern as `system-design/`.

## Conventions

- **TypeScript** in `frontend/`; **plain JS** in `beginner-js/` unless a file already uses something else.
- **Docs:** Prefer updating the closest `README.md` or `docs/codestep/` when behavior or learner-facing flows change.
- **Legacy:** `frontend/init_example.html` is reference-only; the maintained surface is the React app.

When scope spans more than one top-level directory, say which areas you touched and keep cross-links (README, domain READMEs) in sync when behavior changes.
